<div><h3>IDND 103 - Design Your Clark Experience: Connect Your Story to Your Career </h3>  <hr>In this course, students will learn how to customize their Clark experience in a way that prepares them to lead a well-lived and joyful life. Using a process rooted in design thinking, innovation, and positive psychology, students will utilize a growth mindset to face challenges and develop a framework for navigating life decisions. Through readings, short films, podcasts, group discussions, journaling, and creative exercises, students will reflect upon their own personal strengths and values, learn about educational and career opportunities, and create a prototype of their college experience based on their personal definition of success.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Each semester<br><br></div>		</td>
